# Netlify redirects / rewrites for the UKVisaCo static site.
#
# Clean-URL note: Netlify's "Pretty URLs" asset optimization (enabled by default
# in site settings) already serves /about for /about.html. The pages link to each
# other with explicit .html paths (e.g. destinations.html, track.html), so no
# rewrite rules are required for navigation to work. Add explicit aliases here
# only if you later switch the internal links to extension-less paths.
#
# Example (uncomment to force a clean alias without changing the HTML):
# /about    /about.html    200

# 404 fallback — serve the custom 404 page with a real 404 status.
# Must be the LAST rule so it only catches paths nothing else matched.
/*    /404.html    404
